Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(half, peeled and thinly sliced); finely dice remaining half. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{6%teaspoon} (large drizzle for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced shallot and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring, until browned and slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @spinach{5%ounce}; cook, stirring, until wilted, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, half the @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest in Step 5) to same bowl; stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

== Stuffed Salmon with Creamy Spinach ==

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place, skin sides down, on a clean work surface. Using a sharp #knife{}, cut a slit lengthwise down the center of the flesh sides (be careful not to cut through the skin!). Rub all over with a drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper.

> Make sure to season inside the cuts too!

Place salmon, skin sides down, on one side of a second lightly oiled baking sheet. Stuff salmon with spinach filling (it's OK if they seem overstuffed).

Toss asparagus on opposite side of same sheet with a drizzle of oil (large drizzle for 4 servings), remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Roast on middle rack until salmon is cooked though and asparagus is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: If asparagus is done before salmon, remove from sheet and continue roasting salmon.

== Lemon-Shallot Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for spinach over medium heat. Add diced shallot and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until shallot is softened and translucent, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and remaining cream cheese. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in a pinch of lemon zest, juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4), and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted and combined. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide salmon, asparagus, and potatoes between plates. Spoon sauce over salmon. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.